<TITLE> African Nations hosts Ghana storm into FIFA's top 20 </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 BERNE, Feb 13 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - African Nations Cup hosts Ghana climbed 29 places to joint 14th in FIFA's world rankings following their third place finish at the tournament. Ghana are now the highest ranked African nation in the standings, which are published monthly by world soccer's governing body. Cameroon, who lost 1-0 to Egypt in the final, are up eight places to 17th. Egypt are ranked behind Ghana, Cameroon and Ivory Coast at 29th. The top 10 remains largely unchanged due to few competitive internationals in South America and Europe over the last month. FIFA rankings (previous position in brackets) 1. (1.) Argentina 2. (2.) Brazil 3. (3.) Italy 4. (4.) Spain 5. (5.) Germany 6. (6.) Czech Republic 7. (7.) France 8. (8.) Portugal 9. (9.) Netherlands 10. (11.) Greece 11. (12.) England 12. (10.) Croatia 13. (13) Romania 14. (43.) Ghana 14. (14.) Scotland 16. (17.) Mexico 17. (25.) Cameroon 18. (16.) Turkey 19. (18.) Bulgaria 20. (23.) Pola
